\columnbreak

### Worgen Names
Most worgen were Gilnean humans and follow their naming conventions. However, some worgen forgot their past names and lives when the curse turned them feral. These worgen choose a new Gilnean first name and a last name based on feats of strengths done during their cursed worgen life. 


<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

<nr> **Gilnean First Names:** See Human Names and Ethnicities <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; under the Human race.
<br> **Worgen Surnames:** Greymane, Moonfang, Mistmantle, <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bloodfang, Darkwalker

### Worgen Traits
Your worgen character has the following racial traits.

***Creature Type.*** You are a Humanoid. You are also considered a human, a worgen, and a shapeshifter for any prerequisite or effect.

***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Strength score increases by 2, and your Dexterity score increases by 1.

***Age.*** Worgen age like humans, but even though their bodies continue to age, they never feel the strain of old age.

***Alignment.*** Worgen tend to become chaotic, the infection in their blood making them more unpredictable.

***Size.*** Like humans, they vary widely in height and build, most standing well over 6 or 7 feet tall, and weigh around 250 pounds. Your size is Medium.

***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

***Aberration.*** You have advantage on saves against curses and diseases. You count as an Aberration for purposes of animating undead.

***Human Spirit.*** When you roll a 1 on an attack roll, ability check, or saving throw, you can reroll the die. You must use the new result, even if it is a 1.

**_Two Forms._** You are the master of your curse, able to transform between your worgen form and former human form at will over 1 minute. If you die while in your human form, you revert to your worgen form after death. You gain certain the following racial traits when in worgen form:

<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>
 
**Claws.** You can use your claws to make unarmed strikes. 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> When you hit with them, the strike deals 1d6 + your 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> Strength modifier slashing damage, instead of the 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike.
<br> **Climb.** Your sharp claws gives you a climbing speed 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> equal to your movement speed.
<br> **Darkflight.** Your reflexes and agility allow you to move with 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> a burst of speed. When you move on your turn in combat, 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> you can double your speed until the end of the turn. Once 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> you use this trait, you can't use it again until you move 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> 0 feet on one of your turns.
<br> **Darkvision.** Accustomed to the black nights, you have 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You can see 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light, 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> and in darkness as if it were dim light. You can't discern 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> color in darkness, only shades of gray.
<br> **Keen Hearing and Smell.** You have advantage on Wisdom 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> (Perception), Wisdom (Survival), and Intelligence 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> (Investigation) checks that involve hearing or smell.
<br> **Running Wild.** When running on all fours, you can move 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> faster over long distances. When calculating travel pace, 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> you can use twice your movement speed. 
<br> **Standing Leap.** Your long jump is equal to your movement 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> speed and your high jump is equal to 2/3 your movement 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> speed, rounded down to the nearest 5 foot increment, 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> with or without a running start.

