## Dark Iron Dwarf
As a dark iron dwarf, you have a fiery temper and a fierce determination. Dark iron dwarves worshiped the firelord Ragnaros and gained an affinity for fire and flames. 

### Dark Iron Dwarf Traits
Your Dark Iron dwarf character has the following racial traits.

***Creature Type.*** You are a Humanoid. You are also considered a dwarf for any prerequisite or effect that requires you to be a dwarf.

***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Constitution score increases by 2, and your Intelligence score increases by 1.

***Age.*** Dwarves mature at the same rate as humans, but they're considered young until they reach the age of 40. On average, they live about 320 years.

***Alignment.*** Most dwarves are lawful, believing firmly in the benefits of a well-ordered society. They tend toward good as well, with a strong sense of fair play and a belief that all deserve to share in the benefits of a just order.

***Size.*** Dwarves stand between 4 and 5 feet tall and average about 150 pounds. Your size is Medium.

***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 25 feet. Your speed is not reduced by wearing heavy armor.

***Superior Darkvision.*** Accustomed to life underground, you have superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You can see in dim light within 120 feet of you as if it were bright light, and in darkness as if it were dim light. You can't discern color in darkness, only shades of gray.

***Dungeon Delver.*** Without squeezing, you can move through and stop in a space large enough for a Small creature.

***Fireblood.*** As a bonus action you can call upon your resilient ancestry and end either one disease or the poisoned condition on yourself. Your blood feels aflame, increasing your speed by 15 feet and giving you advantage on your next attack roll, until the end of your next turn.  You can use this trait a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.

***Forged in Flame.*** You have resistance to fire damage.

***Mass Production.*** Whenever you make an Intelligence (History) check related to the origin of metalwork or stonework, you are considered proficient in the History skill and add double your proficiency bonus to the check, instead of your normal proficiency bonus.

***Tool Proficiency.*** You gain proficiency with the artisan's tools of your choice: brewer's supplies, cartographer's tools, mason's tools, navigator's tools, or smith's tools.

***Languages.*** You can speak, read, and write Common and Dwarven. Dwarven is full of hard consonants and guttural sounds, and those characteristics spill over into whatever other language a dwarf might speak.

\pagebreak

## High Elf
### Affiliation
**Alliance.**

### High Elf Traits

***TBD.***

\pagebreak

## Highmountain Tauren
As a highmountain tauren, you hail from the Broken Isles. Highmountain taurens have secluded themselves in the isle's mountains for generations. They harbour no hatred towards other races and are generally peaceful and kind hearted. These tauren does not have horns like the rest of their kin, instead they grow large antlers.

### Highmountain Tauren Traits
Your tauren character has the following racial traits.

***Creature Type.*** You are a Humanoid. You are also considered a tauren for any prerequisite or effect that requires you to be a tauren.

***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Strength increases by 2, and your Wisdom score increases by 1.

***Age.*** Tauren reaches adulthood in their mid teens, and most grow to be 95 years old, few live beyond a century. 

***Alignment.*** Most tauren are lawful, keeping to their tribal code. Those who are evil are shunned upon, most either outlaws or corrupted in some form.

***Size.*** Tauren are between 8 and 10 feet tall and weigh between 400 and 600 pounds. Your size is Medium, yet you tower over most other humanoids. 

***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

***Brawn.*** You have proficiency in the Athletics skill, and you count as one size larger when determining your carrying weight and the weight you can push, drag, or lift.

***Goring Rush.*** Immediately after you use the dash action on your turn and move at least 20 feet, you can make one melee attack with your horns as a bonus action.

***Hammering Horns.*** Immediately after you hit a creature with a melee attack as a part of the Attack action on your turn, you can use a bonus action to attempt to shove that target with your horns. The target must be within 5 feet of you and no more than one size larger than you. Unless it succeeds on a Strength saving throw against a DC equal to 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength modifier, you push it up to 10 feet away from you.

***Horns.*** Your horns are natural melee weapons, which you can use to make unarmed strikes. If you hit with them, you deal piercing damage equal to 1d6 + your Strength modifier, instead of the bludgeoning damage normal for an unarmed strike.

***Mountaineer.*** You're acclimated to high altitude, includ&shy;ing elevations above 20,000 feet. You're also naturally adapted to cold climates, as described in chapter 5 of the *Dungeon Master's Guide*.

Additionally, you have advantage on Strength and Dexterity saving throws made against effects that would knock you prone.

***Rugged Tenacity.*** You can draw upon the legacy of your ancestors to shrug off harm. When you take damage, you can use your reaction to roll a d12. Add your Constitution modifier to the number rolled and reduce the damage by that total.

You can use this trait a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.

***Languages.*** You can speak, read, and write Common and Taur-ahe. Taur-ahe is a harsh, and low sounding language, without a proper alphabet, their written language is made of elaborate pictograms and pictoforms.

\pagebreak

## Lightforged Draenei
As a lightforged draenei, you have committed yourself to a crusade against the Burning Legion, infusing your body with the holy light. You are part of the Army of the Light, a force of draenei that took the fight with the Burning Legion into the Twisting Nether and more recently, Azeroth.

### Lightforged Draenei Traits
Your lightforged draenei character has the following racial traits.
 
***Creature Type.*** You are a Humanoid. You are also considered a draenei for any prerequisite or effect that requires you to be a draenei.

***Ability Score Increase.*** Your Charisma score <br> increases by 2, and your Constitution score increases by 1.
 
***Age.*** Draenei mature slightly slower than humans, reach&shy;ing adulthood around age 20 and they can live thousands of year, exceeding the ancient ages of the night elves.

***Alignment.*** Draenei are mostly good. Those who strive towards law are sages, priests, paladins, vindicators, or scholars. Those who tend toward chaos are warriors, rangers, or in other ways people more fond of pure fighting.
 
***Size.*** Draenei are between 7 and 8 feet tall and weigh between 240 and 300 pounds. Your size is Medium. 

***Speed.*** Your base walking speed is 30 feet.

***Gemcutting.*** Due to long familiarity with crystal-based technology, you are proficient with the jeweler's tools. Whenever you make an Intelligence (History) check related to crystals or gemstones, you can add twice your proficiency bonus, instead of any proficiency bonus you would normally apply.
 
***Light's Judgment.*** You know the *light* cantrip; when you cast it with this trait, a sigil of the Naaru appears above your forehead. Starting at 3rd level, you can cast the *divine favor* spell with this trait. Starting 5th level, you can also cast the ✦ *righteous smite* spell with this trait. 

Once you cast *divine favor* or ✦ *righteous smite* with this trait, you can't cast that spell with it again until you finish a long rest. You can also cast either of those spells using any spell slots you have of the appropriate level. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for these spells when you cast them with this trait.

***Light's Reckoning.*** When you are reduced to 0 hit points, your body erupts in a burst of holy light with a 10-foot radius. Each enemy creature within range takes radiant damage equal to 1d8 per level, or half with a successful Dexterity saving throw (DC 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier). You regain use of this ability when you finish a long rest.

***Light's Wrath.*** When you reach 3rd level, choose one of the wrath options below. Thereafter, you can use a bonus action to unleash the celestial energy within yourself, gaining the benefits of that wrath. Your transformation lasts for 1 minute or until you end it as a bonus action. Once you transform using your wrath below, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.

<div style='margin-top:-5px;'></div>

**Forged in the Light.** Spectral constructs of searing light
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> surround you. For the duration, you shed bright light in a 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet, and 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> at the end of each of your turns, each creature within 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> 10 feet of you takes radiant damage equal to your level. 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> Until the transformation ends, once on each of your 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> turns, you can deal extra radiant damage to one target 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> when you deal damage to it with an attack or a spell. The 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> extra damage equals your proficiency bonus.
<br>**Wings of Light.** Two luminous, spectral wings sprout from 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> your back temporarily. Until the transformation ends, you 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> have a flying speed equal to your walking speed, and once 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> on each of your turns, you can deal extra radiant damage 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> to one target when you deal damage to it with an attack 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> or a spell. The extra damage equals your proficiency 
<br><span style="margin-left:11px"></span> bonus.

<br><div style='margin-top:-18px;'></div>

***Radiant Resistance.*** You have resistance to radiant damage.

***Strength of Spirit.*** You have advantage on death saving throws.

***Languages.*** You can speak, read, and write Common and Draenei. The Draenei language, is a strange and compli-cated language for other races to learn. Seemingly having no resemblance with any Azerothian languages.

